The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Trade Unions and the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions will form a strike commission on Friday to coordinate Monday’s strike that will last indefinitely.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day the final vote on the public health law will be held - the work stoppage will begin.
This action will surely cause great difficulties in transport, since the railway traffic will be stopped completely and until 1 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike.
In the afternoon of Friday the League Trade Unions will report on the details of their strike on Monday that will be held jointly with the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions.
The strike committee of the LIGA and the National Union of Machinists will also be formed to coordinate Monday’s actions.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating unions will go on strike indefinitely, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not inform about the date of the end of the strike started.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call for a strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, strike committees will meet and decide on the future.
On Monday's agenda of the National Assembly, it is also possible that the public health law will only be voted on at very late hours of the night, or perhaps near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will start on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: on the railways will stop working indefinitely, in the morning may stop a part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the intercity bus transport of the companies Volán.
At the same time, in many parts of the country, half of the roads will be closed.
Numerous trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League’s website.
Some unions announced their strike for an indefinite time, others for a definite time.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railway and the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) could not reach an agreement even on minimum services, although, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on the trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 13 hours will be on strike the workers of the Collective Transport Company of Budapest, the Airports of Budapest from 7 am to 9 am, will hold a strike of four hours the LIGA Trade Unions of the Electricity and Thermal Energy Industry, the Trade Unions of Educators called for a strike of 2 and the Trade Union of Educators 2 hours.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will go on a national strike at alternative times and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Sector Workers (SDTSSS), which is part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal on public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new way of calculating pensions that will come into force next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, in the case of early pensions, the possibility that deserving occupations can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF), which is part of the League Trade Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the rail sidelines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: In the country the risk is increased by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, established in August this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from several points of view.
The company's "risk warning" reads: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the gypsy and non-gypsy population of Hungary, even in the short term there may be violent ethnic clashes".
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of such an event, added the representative of the research institute.
They stated that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life handed over the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of the radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the existing discrepancies between Roma and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists, and increases the likelihood of violent conflicts.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "significantly damaged the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country."
We are reminded that since the autumn of 2006 the reorganization of Hungary's radical and far-right groups has received increasing publicity and impetus, and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations that call themselves "national self-defense associations" have been formed in the country.
"The common feature of these groups is that they define themselves as civilian organizations, while openly proclaiming the training of their members for defense - even armed - (civil defense, national defense, defense of public order), alluding to the ineptitudes of the police, the army, that is, the state," they add.
They said: all this is done in accordance with the method that tries to give a civil presentation to different political aspirations, based on the dissatisfaction of society with politics and with political parties.
For highlighting the civil and the form of association in the case of these associations not only serves to avoid the legal problems of legal registration, but is at the same time also a political strategy.
According to the analysis, the activity of the Hungarian Guard is a risk factor also from the point of view of neighbourhood relations.
“In recent months, numerous neighbouring states have referred to the Hungarian Guard as a potential danger, while the ultra-nationalist political figures of certain neighbouring countries want to justify their own anti-Hungarian policy with the creation of the Hungarian Guard.
All of this influences the political stability of the region," they added.
According to the research institute, the constitution of the Hungarian Guard is not an isolated phenomenon in Central and Eastern Europe, so political risks increased throughout the region.
They wrote that the Hungarian Guard operates in a similar way as, for example, the Bulgarian National Guard, whose constitution was announced in August 2007 by the far-right Bulgarian National Union (UNB).
The constitution of the Bulgarian guard is due to the mass riots of gypsies that occurred in one of the neighborhoods of Sofia (Krasna Poliana).
Taking advantage of this situation, UNB decided to set up the guard, arguing that the organization's objective is "national self-defense".
In his opinion, in the last 17 years there has been "gypsy terror" in Bulgaria, yet the state remained powerless and indifferent to the facts - remembers the Political Capital.
They added: this initiative has provoked a lively discussion in Bulgarian public opinion.
As written, it indicates the increased risk of ethnic clashes which certain Roma organizations in Bulgaria have announced that in order to resist, they will constitute their own guard.
As the operation of the Hungarian Guard has so far shown similarities to that of the Bulgarian National Guard, it cannot be excluded that the Hungarian Gypsies also react to the threat in a similar way, organizing their own self-defense - it can be read in the warning about the risks of Political Capital.
Political Capital research director Attila Juhász told the news agency: risk analysis is one of the activities of the research institute.
As he said, every year they publish their risk analysis and when they experience something that can influence the change in risk, they inform the public, as happened in this case, by publishing their warning about the risks.
The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers in the calendar and it has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - which next year will be less - workdays are reorganized.
Even in the EU or North America, the holidays are not unitary.
Hungarian laws make a difference between a national holiday, a state holiday and a public holiday.
The holidays are mainly related to religious holidays and historical ephemeris.
We celebrate the New Year too: both the last day of the old year, as well as the first day of the new year is festive - the latter especially so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven holidays written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and on October 23, commemorating the 1956 revolution.
On August 20th we celebrate the foundation of the State, on May 1st the Labor Day, on November 1st and 2nd we remember our deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, in our country there are two-day festivals, Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, which is why we often bridge when there is only one working day before or after the holiday.
In exchange for extended weekends, during the previous Saturdays you can not be absent from work or school.
It is the minister of labour who regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the feast.
This legal standard is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public officials.
On the other hand, it is not mandatory for companies and service institutions which, due to their function, work uninterruptedly even during the holidays.
This year the order of work can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from 24 December, life in the country practically stops, since according to experiences, most people "bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
Next year several of our holidays will coincide with mid or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working days than this year.
First, the agenda around the Labor Day will be modified so that then, for four successive days, workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26th will be a working day, so that in exchange Friday, May 2nd will be a festive day.
The other change relates to the feast of October 23: on Saturday, October 18, you will have to work instead of Friday, October 24.
On the other hand, next year during the holidays you can rest, since from December 24 will not work almost anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
6 Small Deterrents to Bitter Your Colleagues' Lives
Emails that we forget to send, sound messages that we never receive, innocent lies that pass us by without realizing: all of them are part of our daily Folklore at work.
You have to decide if you adapt to small discomforts or consciously avoid confusing situations that can irritate others.
Advice.
I'm sorry, I forgot to let you know that you've been picked up from the marketing department," says one of your colleagues.
That's why you didn't go on a date?
At best he feels it and tries to fix the matter, maybe call the marketing department to tell them that he forgot to deliver the message to you (this is the less common solution).
Most of the time the matter is settled by apologizing.
Before proceeding to embarrassing explanations, it is worth meditating on the things with which you can bitteren up the lives of your colleagues and consciously strive to avoid them.
Do you borrow something that is not yours?
There is nothing more irritating than when you want to pick up a document, an office tool or your phone and you can’t find them.
Remember yesterday you put the stapler on the table, but for this morning it disappeared?
Do you find your lost pen on the table of one of your colleagues?
Do not take anything away from your colleagues without asking them, because they will rightly be angry with you for stealing their things.
Do not take envelopes or post-it from the office because it may be unpleasant when you need them immediately and they run out ahead of time.
Are you gossiping about your colleagues' private lives?
There is no good solution to stop rumors that are already running.
Who, what is he doing and with whom?
Where and why?
Do not pass on to everyone the information (conjectures) you have about the private life of your colleagues!
Don’t abuse your colleague’s trust when he shares his innermost secrets with you!
Bury in yourself what you have heard and do not gossip about your colleague in his absence, even if others also know the things about him.
Are you on sick leave unjustifiably?
When you call the office and say that you are sick and your head hurts unbearably, you feel bad or good, you feel that that day you prefer to rest; think about what others should do your work, your unscheduled tasks, your work for term.
Don't bother your colleague!
If you know in advance that the next day you will not go to the office or something may happen to you, so you should stay at home, let them know, so that your colleagues or your boss do not have to confront your absence the next day.
Screams, laughter, phone calls
Are you involved in your work, but suddenly get rid of the laughter of your colleagues?
Have you ever involuntarily heard a phone conversation that would have been better not to hear?
Do not annoy your colleagues with your rattles, chants, conversations aloud (less when you do them above their head), kicking, constant blasphemies, expressing your discontents aloud.
All these can be annoying, even if they are not deepening at the moment in a project (writing, planning, organization).
Are you blaming others for a mistake?
Don’t blame others if you haven’t finished something on time, forgot to send an important letter or message!
Don’t allude to the chaos that eventually reigns in the office, or to the noise that your colleagues make!
You must recognize if you have made a mistake that harms others and you must repair the fault!
Ask how you can fix your fault!
Do you feel too much at home in the office?
Jogging and Sneakers: Very comfortable habit for the house, but not suitable for the office!
Don’t wear a comfortable jog even if your occupation allows it!
Don’t be distracted, respect your colleagues and yourself by wearing everyday, elegant and beautiful clothes when your occupation demands it!
