Six hundred thousand drivers missed the date and for this reason they did not manage to change their old driving license whose validity ends at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when people can request the change so that officials give them time until the end of the year to issue the new card.
However, the Ministry does not fear that after New Year hundreds of thousands of drivers will be on the roads without a valid driver’s license.
According to traffic, the passport has not been changed mainly by those who no longer even want to drive.
While in the villages they announce a rapid decline in the change of card, the offices of the metropolis are full of applications and interest in the new card has increased.
The City Council estimates around 2,000 daily customers.
In the queues wait half an hour.
In Prague, around 140,000 drivers have not yet been issued the new driver’s license.
The issuance of a new card lasts twenty days.
However, it is possible to request the issuance of the card within a shorter period of five days.
But in that case the driver must pay five hundred crowns.
Drivers who must change their driving license and do not reach until the end of the year, but will go on the roads without a valid driving license will risk a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand crowns.
The police can fix the infraction with a warning.
In case of an administrative infraction the fine will amount to 2,500 crowns.
According to the above information, a person who does not go anywhere could receive a fine.
They could presumably pay up to 30,000 kroner.
The Ministry appealed to the offices to moderately impose fines of up to 1,000 kroner.
According to transport ministry spokesman Karel Hanzelka, the 1,000 kroner fines do not threaten anyone.
According to him, the driver’s license is a document in which people can decide whether they want it or not.
It is not the identity card that each person must have valid.
People who don’t want to drive should hand over their driver’s license.
Just bring it or send it by registered mail to the municipal offices.
At the end of the year, the cards issued during the years 1964 and 1993 cease to be valid.
However, drivers will have to gradually change the other types of driver’s license.
People with the document between 1994 and 2000 have up to three years to change it.
The validity of the card that was issued between the years 2001 and 2004 ends in December 2013.
