In 1999, Melvin Benn added the Leeds Festival to his portfolio then, in 2006, the Republic Festival created the Latitude Henham Park Festival in Suffolk.
Since 2002, as co-owner, Melvin Benn has also been in charge of the production, licensing and organizational tasks of the Glastonbury Festival, which can now host up to 177,500 people.
Calling Glastonbury the "most inspiring event" I've ever attended, Charlie Jones of C3 says his company and Melvin Benn's work together to give the region a European-style festival-event.
