Both events recorded respective gross revenues of $9.8M and $11.3M in 2007.
These two festivals take place in an urban environment.
“Melvin Benn’s European model is a country festival, while ours is more about urban green spaces,” says Charlie Jones.
The aim is to merge, in one way or another, both formulas to give both an impression of country festival in the European and urban in the American way. "
Vineland is roughly halfway between Philadelphia and Atlantic City.
"The Vineland community, including the mayor, enthusiastically supports the celebration of this event," says Charlie Jones.
