The Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which came into force November 1
Parallel to its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the vote by Congress of the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim of having both enter into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations in order to guarantee the protection of investors and regulate in detail the activity of the entities so that the markets function efficiently.
The MIFID, which amends the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of financial markets, while reinforcing investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and encouraging cooperation between the various supervisors of the European Union.
The new rules will allow financial advisory services to be provided to both specialised firms and to natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory firms (FIAs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions in financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are joined by multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment firms to disclose in the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management forms and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they make, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage through the Economics Committee of Congress, several modifications were incorporated, among which it is worth noting that securitised debts are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given their high danger to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the debt of U.S. high-risk mortgages (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally define the functions that graduates in Economics and Business can perform 30 years after the Royal Decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists was approved in 1977.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work as an employee, will not require authorization from the CNMV and will be able to provide its product marketing and customer acquisition services to different investment companies at the same time.
