That in theory should reduce the risk of a rapid asset downgrade.
“We’re not going to wake up one day and reassess all the loans,” says Gary Perlin, head of finance at Capital One.
If a sudden subprime infection in the credit card market is unlikely, the risks of a sustained decline are much more real.
