It's not the wooden boxes.
Whoever relates the terms Sweden and wooden box, thinks of Ikea, but does not think of Andy Warhol.
Isn't that so?
Currently the wooden boxes produced in Sweden are like the shadow that weighs on Warhol’s list of works.
Most of the ninety-four Shine-Boxes on this list are fake.
After a few months ago the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" cast doubt on the authenticity of Andy Warhol's 1968 Brilliance-Boxes, the Moderna Museet museum in Stockholm conducted internal research and came to disappointing conclusions: the six "Brightness-Boxes", which the former director of the museum Pontus Hultén also gifted to the museum Moderna Museet, are "false one hundred of the international market", and almost one hundred of them.
Prehistory is too complicated with a confusing relationship between artistic and sponsored productions.
In 1964 Warhol created in New York his first "Bright-Boxes", he painted the wooden boxes in red, blue and white, with the same sample that had cartons of soap powder "Bright".
According to Warhol, in the exhibition of his works of 1968 in the Moderna Museet museum were exhibited hundreds of Shine-cardboard boxes. These were not made by Warhol (because of the expenses), but were brought directly from the cardboard factory of "Brillo".
These were not works of art, but exemplars (which were only objects) on display.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed to produce in Sweden a Gloss-wooden boxes, but they were not exhibited in the Modern Museet museum.
Witnesses of those times now speak of almost fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auctions as originals of the "Brillo-Boxes" of "Stockholm type" authorized by Andy Warhol.
At auction some of them were bought for more than $100,000.
The problem is that after the famous director of the museum Pontus Hultén made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden were produced and exposed almost a hundred of the wooden boxes that Warhol left to him.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 in Malmö for Hultén and for the exhibition in St. Petersburg.
By this time Warhol had already died for 3 years.
Lars Byström, the chief curator of the Moderna Museet museum, investigated six Bright Boxes owned by the museum and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm. First their tight silvers were printed and grinded and then painted in oil with the brush.
On the contrary, the structure of the copies of the year 1990 shows that the paint was applied with a roller without directly printing the tight silvers. In addition, it is not about oil painting, but about acrylic painting.
“These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and must be removed from Andy Warhol’s official Brilliance-Boxes list,” says Lars Nittve, the director of the Moderna Museet museum and adds that if The Andy Warhol Art Authentication Commission in New York does not come to any conclusion, the Moderna Museet museum will classify these six boxes as the exhibition copies/objects.”
Already in July the Authentication Commission formally announced that it accepts these "serious accusations" that these are soap powder boxes.
But from that moment there everything remained in absolute silence.
Rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
In the Philippines, rebel soldiers who had entrenched themselves in a hotel in Manila and demanded the overthrow of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo have surrendered.
The leader Antonio Trillanes, who blames the president for corruption and electoral fraud, told a reporter that he could not answer for shedding blood.
The soldiers loyal to the government had stormed the hotel using tear gas.
Nearly two hundred soldiers had been barricading themselves in the building for a few hours.
Almost half of them, including Trillanes, were on trial Thursday for attempting a coup in 2003 that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, to suddenly be able to deposit himself with about 30 supporters.
Evidently the military policemen who were to watch him had passed into his ranks and followed his mutiny.
They entered the "Peninsula" hotel and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blockaded the neighborhood around the Noble Hotel.
The president called an urgent session of the Security Cabinet.
Norberto Gonzales, the National Security Advisor, condemned the behavior of the soldiers.
“People are fed up,” Trillanes said.
“We call on people to come into our ranks.”
Gen. Danilo Lim, who formerly led the elite Scout Reangers troop, said the other military troops soon wanted to follow the march.
Major government critics called for a major demonstration against the president on Thursday.
For months his government has been criticized for corruption.
In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all the attention for the mutiny that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986, there have been at least seven attempted coups in the Philippines against the democratically elected government.
United Internet will be Versatel’s largest shareholder.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares of telecommunications company Versatel.
On Wednesday, the company reported that the average price for a share is 14.46 euros.
It holds only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There was much speculation about the company’s absorption.
There are also options for further increasing the financial part at Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German DSL (Digital Subscriber Line) market.
On Wednesday they already made assumptions about entering the business, after the bank Brendenberg increased its stake in the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market that means that the financial institution holds equity securities for a third-party partner.
United Internet already on the previous day involved with almost 10 by hundreds the telecommunications company Drillisch.
Drillich in the capital increase measure placed 17.4 million of the new shares with a value of 106.4 million euros.
United Internet has bought 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, the companies began negotiations on DSL-products marketing cooperations.
“We are strengthening our partnership,” said a United Internet spokesperson.
The two companies founded a joint venture MSP, to acquire the competitor Freenet.
On Thursday, United Internet reported that at the beginning, the two companies want to be happy with the ten percent stake in Freenet and do not make use of their right, that is, they make 18.49 per hundred of Freenet participate.
That meant that both companies kept all options, especially participation in the Freenet corporation.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
Until now the holding of United Internet and Drillich had directly 6.01 percent of the stake in Freenet.
Then they had agreed that Drillisch is going to achieve the other four percent.
The right to buy 18.49 percent of the investment company Vatas was already agreed in August.
